matrix notation
\[
\begin{align*}
\textbf{y}\sim& \text{Normal}(\boldsymbol{\mu},\sigma)\\
\boldsymbol{\mu} =& \text{g}^{-1}(\textbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta})\\
\text{g}(\boldsymbol{\mu}) =&   \textbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}
\end{align*}
\]


\[\begin{align*}

\textbf{y} =
\begin{bmatrix}
y_{1} \\
y_{2} \\
y_{3} \\
. \\
. \\
y_{n}  
\end{bmatrix}


\textbf{X} =
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & x_{1,2} & x_{1,3} \\
1 & x_{2,2} & x_{2,3} \\
1 & x_{3,2} & x_{3,3} \\
. & . .\\
. & . .\\
n & x_{n,2} & x_{n,3}
\end{bmatrix}

\boldsymbol{\beta} = \begin{bmatrix}
\beta_0 \\
\beta_1 \\
\beta_2 \\
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}\]
n = sample size x\(_{2}\) & x\(_{3}\) are independent variables

Logistic Regression (logit link)
\[
\begin{align*}
